SIMPLE: programma
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Programma
<hw>Pro*gram"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Programmata</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[ L. See
<er>Programme</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>Any law, which, after it had
passed the Athenian senate, was fixed on a tablet for public inspection
previously to its being proposed to the general assembly of the
people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An edict published for public information; an
official bulletin; a public proclamation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>See <er>Programme</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A preface.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>T.
Warton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Programme</ent>⟦br⟧
